NAME             vimrc -- Vim configuration

SYNOPSIS         vim [file ...]

DESCRIPTION      Vimrc configures Vim for files and directories.
                 File buffers edit text.
                 Directory buffers list entries; directories end in /.
                 Plumbing resolves text in this order: quickfix or location
                 jump, URL, wiki link, readable file:line, readable file,
                 directory, search.
                 Relative plumbs resolve against the supplied working
                 directory.
                 File buffers supply expand('%:h').
                 Directory buffers supply b:dir.
                 :Cmd runs in the current buffer directory.

MOUSE            Vim sets mouse=nv.

                 Mouse button     Action
                 1                select text
                 1 status col 1   grow window, on a status line
                 double 1         expand bracket, quote object, or word
                 double 1 status  close window, on a status line
                 C-1 status       zoom window, on a status line only
                 2                execute <cWORD>
                 2 visual         execute selection
                 2 status         resize or zoom window
                 3                plumb word/WORD
                 3 visual         plumb selection

                 Button 2 appends stdout and stderr to +Errors.
                 Button 3 uses the plumbing order in DESCRIPTION.

DIRECTORIES      A directory buffer lists one entry per line.
                 b:dir names its directory.
                 Relative plumbs resolve against b:dir.
                 Global - opens the current directory.
                 <leader>B toggles the directory browser.

                 Key              Action
                 <CR>             open or reuse entry
                 <leader><CR>     plumb entry
                 <RightMouse>     plumb entry
                 <MiddleMouse>    execute entry
                 <C-LeftMouse>    execute entry
                 -                go up
                 R                reload
                 <leader>r        rename entry
                 <leader>d        delete entry
                 <C-j>            next window or tmux pane

COMMANDS         :Cmd [-range] [cmd]
                      Run cmd asynchronously with /bin/sh -c.
                      Send the addressed lines on stdin.
                      Append stdout and stderr to +Errors.

                 :Lint [filetype]
                      Run the linter for filetype.
                      Append output to +Errors.

                 :Fmt [-range=%] [filetype]
                      Run the formatter for filetype.
                      Replace the addressed range or whole buffer.

                 :Fts [args...]
                      Run external fts.
                      Fill the location list.

                 :Toc [pattern]
                      Fill the location list with an outline.
                      Use pattern, or the filetype default.

                 :Sort
                      Sort named visible windows by buffer name.

                 :B /regex/[dD]
                      List matching buffers.
                      Delete them with d or D.

                 :Dump [file]
                      Write session state.
                      Default file is getcwd()/vim.dump.

                 :Load [file]
                      Read session state.
                      Default file is getcwd()/vim.dump.

                 :Send [-range] [tmux-target]
                      Send lines to a tmux pane.
                      Remember tmux-target per window.

KEYS             Leader is space.
                 Tmux crossing requires $TMUX and a Vim window edge.

                 Key              Action
                 <leader>!        prompt for shell command
                 <leader>.        lcd to file directory
                 <leader>;        send line to tmux
                 <leader><CR>     plumb word
                 <leader><leader> expand selection
                 <leader>B        toggle directory browser
                 <leader>D        dump session
                 <leader>E        dump session and quit all
                 <leader>N        edit new file in file directory
                 <leader>c        comment operator
                 <leader>cc       comment line
                 <leader>f        format buffer
                 <leader>l        lint buffer
                 <leader>q        close buffer
                 <leader>Q        force close buffer
                 <leader>y        yank relative path by OSC 52
                 <leader>Y        yank absolute path by OSC 52
                 <leader>z        zoom window
                 -                open current directory
                 <C-j>            next Vim window; tmux at last
                 <C-k>            previous Vim window; tmux at first
                 <C-l>            clear search and redraw
                 <C-p>            run :FZF
                 +                grow window height

                 Visual Key       Action
                 <leader>!        execute selection
                 <leader>;        send selection to tmux
                 <leader><CR>     plumb selection
                 *                search selection

                 Go Key           Action
                 <leader>gc       GoCallers
                 <leader>gd       GoDeclsDir
                 <leader>gi       GoInfo
                 <leader>gt       GoTestFile -v

                 Terminal Key     Action
                 <C-j>            next Vim window; tmux at last
                 <C-k>            previous Vim window; tmux at first
                 <leader>z        zoom window

                 Bracket          Action
                 ]a [a            next/previous argument
                 ]b [b            next/previous buffer
                 ]l [l            next/previous location
                 ]q [q            next/previous quickfix
                 ]t [t            next/previous tab

                 Toggle           Option
                 yob              background
                 yoh              hlsearch
                 yoi              ignorecase
                 yol              list
                 yon              number
                 yop              paste
                 yor              relativenumber
                 yos              spell
                 yow              wrap

FILES            getcwd()/vim.dump
                      default session file for :Dump and :Load

                 +Errors
                      scratch buffer for command output

ENVIRONMENT      Vim 9.1+ is required.
                 $TMUX lets <C-j> and <C-k> cross Vim window edges.
                 OSC 52 path yanks write to /dev/tty.
                 OSC 52 path yanks need terminal support and one of base64,
                 openssl, or python3.
                 The Vim clipboard option is not used.

SEE ALSO         vim(1), acme(1), plumber(4)

OWNER            callemo
